message.content: If Harmony made each notepad with 5 letter size pieces of paper folded three times, that means she created a total of 5 * (2^3) = 5 * 8 = 40 smaller note papers per notepad. If someone wrote ten notes per day and each notepad had 40 pages, then one notepad would last for 40 / 10 = 4 days. So, one notepad would last for four days if someone wrote ten notes per day.
